  "text": "The present study continues a line of research assessing the correspondence of linguistic structures with patterns of cognitive behavior. The original research [CITATION_1] ) explored the ways structural differences between American English and Yucatec Maya (an indigenous language of Mexico) related to the cognition of adult speakers of those languages. Specifically, the research focused on the patterned relationship between grammatical number marking and responses on memory and classification tasks involving pictures and objects.",
